org.svvrl.goal.core.aut.opt

Class EfficientDelayedSimulation

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.svvrl.goal.core.aut.opt.EfficientDelayedSimulation

  • public class EfficientDelayedSimulation
extends java.lang.Object
    This class provides a much more efficient computation of delayed simulation compared to DelayedSimulation. Instead of Game used in DelayedSimulation, this class uses a simpler structure SimpleParityGame.
    Author:
    Ming-Hsien Tsai

    • Method Detail

      • getDelayedSimulationGame

        public SimpleParityGame getDelayedSimulationGame(FSA aut,
                                                 java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,Pair<State,State>> map)
        Returns a simple parity game used to compute the delayed simulation relation of a Büchi automaton.
        Parameters:
        aut - a Büchi automaton
        map - a map for storing the mapping from a state s of the returned simple parity game to a pair of a state s1 in aut and a state s2 in aut which determines s1 is delayed simulated by s2 if s is in the winning region of GamePlayer.P0
        Returns:
        a simple parity game used to compute the delayed simulation relation of the Büchi automata
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if aut is not a Büchi automaton

      • getDelayedSimulationGame

        public SimpleParityGame getDelayedSimulationGame(FSA aut1,
                                                 FSA aut2,
                                                 java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,Pair<State,State>> map)
        Returns a simple parity game used to compute the delayed simulation relation of two Büchi automata.
        Parameters:
        aut1 - a Büchi automaton
        aut2 - a Büchi automaton
        map - a map for storing the mapping from a state s of the returned simple parity game to a pair of a state s1 in aut1 and a state s2 in aut2 which determines s1 is delayed simulated by s2 if s is in the winning region of GamePlayer.P0
        Returns:
        a simple parity game used to compute the delayed simulation relation of the Büchi automata
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if aut1 or aut2 is not a Büchi automaton, the automata have different alphabet type, or the automata have different label position

      • getDelayedSimulationRelation

        public Relation<State> getDelayedSimulationRelation(FSA aut)
        Returns the delayed simulation relation of a Büchi automaton. If (s1, s2) is in the returned relation, then s1 is delayed simulated by s2.
        Parameters:
        aut - a Büchi automaton
        Returns:
        the delayed simulation relation of the Büchi automaton
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if aut is not a Büchi automaton

      • getDelayedSimulationRelation

        public Relation<State> getDelayedSimulationRelation(FSA aut1,
                                                    FSA aut2)
        Returns the delayed simulation relation of two Büchi automata. If (s1, s2) is in the returned relation, then s1 in the first automaton is delayed simulated by s2 in the second automaton.
        Parameters:
        aut1 - a Büchi automaton
        aut2 - a Büchi automaton
        Returns:
        the delayed simulation relation of the Büchi automata
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if aut1 or aut2 is not a Büchi automaton, the automata have different alphabet type, or the automata have different label position
